### Version

Yosys 0.52+32 (git sha1 9d3d0a433, clang++ 14.0.0-1ubuntu1.1 -fsanitize=address -fsanitize=undefined -fPIC -O3 -O1 -fno-omit-frame-pointer -fno-optimize-sibling-calls -fsanitize=address,undefined)

### On which OS did this happen?

Linux

### Reproduction Steps

Below is the Verilog code `test.v` that triggers the issue:

```verilog
`timescale 1ns/1ps
module a (in2, out2);

input wire in2;
output wire out2;

assign out2 = (7'b11100 / ({1'b1, in2}));

endmodule
```

The following command is used for conversion:

```bash
yosys -p "read_verilog test.v; write_cxxrtl test.cpp"
```

Then, the `main.cpp` file is written for simulation:

```cpp
#include <fstream>
#include <iostream>
#include <sstream>
#include <vector>
#include <string>
#include "test.cpp"

using namespace std;
using namespace cxxrtl_design;

int main() {
    std::unique_ptr<p_a> mod = std::make_unique<p_a>();

    mod->step();
    mod->p_in2 = cxxrtl::value<1>(10000u);
    cout << mod->p_in2.val() << std::endl; // 1'2710

    mod->step();
    cout << mod->p_out2.val() << std::endl;

    return 0;
}
```

The following command is used for compilation:

```bash
clang++ -w -g -O3 -std=c++14 -I $(yosys-config --datdir)/include/backends/cxxrtl/runtime main.cpp -o a.out
```

Running `./a.out` results in the following error:

```
a.out: /usr/local/share/yosys/include/backends/cxxrtl/runtime/cxxrtl/cxxrtl.h:612: std::pair<value<Bits>, value<Bits>> cxxrtl::value<7>::udivmod(value<Bits>) const [Bits = 7]: Assertion `divisor_shift >= 0' failed.
Aborted (core dumped)
```

I believe the issue is related to https://github.com/YosysHQ/yosys/issues/5042, where CXXRTL does not truncate out-of-range values during assignment, leading to an error during division:

```cpp
p_out2 = div_uu<7>(value<7>{0x1cu}, value<6>{0x1u}.concat(p_in2).val()).slice<0>().val();
```

I inspected the `cxxrtl.h` file and located the error. By adding print statements, I found that `divisor.ctlz()` produces an abnormally large number:

```cpp
std::pair<value<Bits>, value<Bits>> udivmod(value<Bits> divisor) const {
    value<Bits> quotient;
    value<Bits> dividend = *this;
    if (dividend.ucmp(divisor))
        return {/*quotient=*/value<Bits>{0u}, /*remainder=*/dividend};

    std::cout << dividend.val() << " " << divisor.val() << std::endl;
    std::cout << dividend.ctlz() << " " << divisor.ctlz() << std::endl;

    int64_t divisor_shift = divisor.ctlz() - dividend.ctlz();
    assert(divisor_shift >= 0);
    divisor = divisor.shl(value<Bits>{(chunk::type) divisor_shift});
    for (size_t step = 0; step <= divisor_shift; step++) {
        quotient = quotient.shl(value<Bits>{1u});
        if (!dividend.ucmp(divisor)) {
            dividend = dividend.sub(divisor);
            quotient.set_bit(0, true);
        }
        divisor = divisor.shr(value<Bits>{1u});
    }
    return {quotient, /*remainder=*/dividend};
}
```

The output is as follows:

```
7'1c 7'2712
2 18446744073709551609
```

### Expected Behavior

The simulation should complete successfully.

### Actual Behavior

Simulation failed

